345
00:16:32,484 --> 00:16:35,278
Hey, Grandpa. Don't you
think that's too easy?

346
00:16:35,278 --> 00:16:37,405
I know what I'm doing.

347
00:16:37,405 --> 00:16:39,658
Okay, I'm sure this
can't be that hard.

348
00:16:48,583 --> 00:16:51,962
I don't think I'm strong
enough to do it!

349
00:16:51,962 --> 00:16:53,129
What does she mean?

350
00:16:53,129 --> 00:16:54,798
Does she have some kind
of muscle disease?

351
00:16:54,798 --> 00:16:56,591
You stop the scaring of Apachai!

352
00:16:56,591 --> 00:16:57,968
Man, that's just sad.

353
00:16:57,968 --> 00:17:02,806
She's gotta be one hardcore nerd
if she can't do a single pushup.

354
00:17:02,806 --> 00:17:04,224
Izumi.

355
00:17:08,937 --> 00:17:10,689
Maybe I can't use
a chain sickle,

356
00:17:10,689 --> 00:17:12,274
but I am certainly swift.

357
00:17:12,315 --> 00:17:14,734
I'd like to see her
try to run so fast.

358
00:17:27,914 --> 00:17:31,860
I can't do it! I tried as
hard as I could, but I can't!

359
00:17:35,213 --> 00:17:37,507
Hey, it's okay, Izumi.

360
00:17:37,507 --> 00:17:39,134
You shouldn't beat
yourself up about it.

361
00:17:39,134 --> 00:17:42,095
But I think it's probably a good
idea if you don't join the dojo.

362
00:17:42,095 --> 00:17:44,180
We're not joking,
it's easy to die here.

363
00:17:50,854 --> 00:17:53,064
This, is like some
stupid nightmare.

364
00:17:53,064 --> 00:17:56,359
Why does that crazy
chick keep following me?

365
00:17:56,359 --> 00:17:57,736
It's because.

366
00:17:57,736 --> 00:17:59,154
Run.

367
00:18:03,950 --> 00:18:04,784
There we go!

368
00:18:04,784 --> 00:18:07,704
I lost her with my patented
ninety-degree corner maneuver!

369
00:18:15,754 --> 00:18:18,173
Did I manage to shake
her for good?

370
00:18:31,826 --> 00:18:33,265
C'mon, really?

371
00:18:33,265 --> 00:18:35,225
Don't tell me that you're
actually that weak.

372
00:18:35,225 --> 00:18:37,311
I only hit you with one finger.

373
00:18:37,311 --> 00:18:38,729
I'm. fine.

374
00:18:38,729 --> 00:18:43,734
That's what I like to
hear. Now act like it.

375
00:18:43,734 --> 00:18:47,946
Oh did you run into
my finger again?

376
00:18:47,946 --> 00:18:49,239
Alright then!

377
00:18:51,408 --> 00:18:52,534
I made you some tea.

378
00:18:52,534 --> 00:18:53,952
Thanks. That's just
what I needed.

379
00:18:53,952 --> 00:18:56,538
I'm sorry I acted like such
an immature brat earlier.

380
00:18:56,538 --> 00:18:59,166
I'm embarrassed. I don't
know what came over me.

381
00:18:59,166 --> 00:19:02,461
Same here. I'm really
sorry I was so rude.

382
00:19:08,133 --> 00:19:11,136
I hope this doesn't sound mean,
but I think Kenichi might have

383
00:19:11,136 --> 00:19:12,554
a stronger aptitude
for gardening

384
00:19:12,554 --> 00:19:14,515
than he does for this
martial arts stuff.

385
00:19:14,515 --> 00:19:15,224
Definitely.

386
00:19:15,224 --> 00:19:17,059
You know, the masters
here are always saying

387
00:19:17,059 --> 00:19:19,478
he doesn't have any natural
talent for Martial Arts.

388
00:19:19,478 --> 00:19:21,772
But then, why does he do it?

389
00:19:21,772 --> 00:19:24,191
Um, I guess it's because he
just got sick and tired

390
00:19:24,191 --> 00:19:27,110
of running away all the time.

391
00:19:27,110 --> 00:19:28,779
Yeah, before he joined the dojo

392
00:19:28,779 --> 00:19:30,489
he used to run away
from everything.

393
00:19:30,489 --> 00:19:36,411
But I think he realized he was
running from his own fear.

394
00:19:36,411 --> 00:19:37,746
Okay, I'm done.

395
00:19:37,746 --> 00:19:40,582
And who said you
get to decide that?

396
00:19:40,582 --> 00:19:44,586
Get up! You at least have to
stand on your feet to run away!

397
00:19:44,586 --> 00:19:46,380
What? What'd you say?

398
00:19:46,380 --> 00:19:48,924
Who's running away?

399
00:19:55,430 --> 00:19:57,474
I don't know if that
made any sense,

400
00:19:57,474 --> 00:19:59,434
but you got the
right spirit kid.

401
00:20:08,068 --> 00:20:10,154
Wow, they have a
hot springs back here?

402
00:20:10,154 --> 00:20:12,656
I bet people would be willing
to pay an admission for this.

403
00:20:12,656 --> 00:20:14,324
Especially if I told
them that it had

404
00:20:14,324 --> 00:20:15,826
some type of healing properties.

405
00:20:22,082 --> 00:20:25,586
How many times can
I fall for this?

406
00:20:25,586 --> 00:20:30,924
Are you ever gonna get bored
with trying to kill me?!

407
00:20:30,924 --> 00:20:33,427
I'm sorry for interrupting
your training, Kenichi.

408
00:20:33,427 --> 00:20:34,428
It won't happen again.

409
00:20:34,428 --> 00:20:35,637
Don't worry about it, Izumi.

410
00:20:35,637 --> 00:20:39,600
You know, young lady, I think
you learned something today.

411
00:20:39,600 --> 00:20:41,894
Was there anything about
watching Kenichi's training

412
00:20:41,894 --> 00:20:44,855
that made you recognize
something about yourself?

413
00:20:44,855 --> 00:20:46,356
There was.

414
00:20:46,356 --> 00:20:48,775
Despite what it looks like,
training isn't just about

415
00:20:48,775 --> 00:20:51,111
strengthening your physicality
or defending yourself.

416
00:20:51,111 --> 00:20:53,071
In fact, the most
important thing is that

417
00:20:53,071 --> 00:20:57,367
it teaches you to
think with your heart.

418
00:20:57,367 --> 00:20:59,077
Make sure you come
back to see us.

419
00:20:59,077 --> 00:21:00,704
You're welcome any time.

420
00:21:00,704 --> 00:21:03,165
And if you change your
mind, take my entry test.

421
00:21:03,165 --> 00:21:04,499
It's much easier.

422
00:21:04,499 --> 00:21:06,835
Thanks so much,
everyone. Bye, Kenichi.

423
00:21:06,835 --> 00:21:07,878
I'll see you tomorrow.

424
00:21:07,878 --> 00:21:10,923
Bye, Izumi. See you
at school tomorrow.

425
00:21:14,384 --> 00:21:16,887
Oh, man, I don't know what
I would do if Izumi actually

426
00:21:16,887 --> 00:21:19,598
joined the dojo. I think
